## ðŸ“… Week 1 Tasks

### ðŸ”¹ 1. Problem Definition
The goal of this project is to predict the **potability of water** (safe = 1, unsafe = 0) using machine learning techniques.  
This supports sustainability by promoting clean and safe water consumption practices.

### ðŸ”¹ 2. Dataset Collection
- **Dataset Name:** Water Potability Dataset  
- **Source (Kaggle):** [https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/adityakadiwal/water-potability](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/adityakadiwal/water-potability)  
- **Attributes:**  
  `pH`, `Hardness`, `Solids`, `Chloramines`, `Sulfate`, `Conductivity`, `Organic_carbon`, `Trihalomethanes`, `Turbidity`, `Potability`

### ðŸ”¹ 3. Data Preprocessing
- Loaded dataset using `pandas`
- Checked for missing and duplicate values  
- Filled missing values with the column mean  
- Removed duplicates if any  
- Verified datatypes and basic statistics  

### ðŸ”¹ 4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Visualized data distributions using **histograms and boxplots**  
- Checked feature correlations using **heatmaps**  
- Observed how each parameter affects water potability  

